). Striae uniseriate, composed of irregularly placed, transapically elongated, slit-like areolae (
<figureCitation box="[832,918,1588,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="3.[136,243,947,969]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,190,923]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[177,1411,190,923]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Stauroneis lacuspowaiensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, external valve views. 9, 10. External views of an entire valve. 11, 13. Terminal raphe fissures continuing on mantle. 12. Stauros with straight central raphe ends. 14. Irregularly placed areolae (double arrowheads). Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 9, 10, 12); 1 µm (Figs 11, 13, 14)." pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
