<figureCitation box="[1304,1438,1587,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="3.[136,243,1994,2016]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,1067,1970]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[170,1417,1067,1970]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Stauroneis lacuspowaiensis Wadmare &amp; B.Karthick nom. nov., stat. nov., SEM, internal valve views. 15. Internal view of an entire valve. 15, 17. Elevated stauros possessing tunnel gap (arrowheads). 17.Areolae irregular covered with hymen structures (double arrowheads). 16, 18. Terminal raphe fissures with helictoglossae. Scale bars = 4 µm (Figs 15–18)." pageId="2" pageNumber="44">Figs 15–18</figureCitation>
